<item>
            <title>[FLINK-14747] Performance regression with latest changes to Mailbox</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-14747</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The commits &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/commit/edeec8d7420185d1c49b2739827bd921d2c2d485&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;edeec8d7420185d1c49b2739827bd921d2c2d485&lt;/a&gt; .. &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/commit/809533e5b5c686e2d21b64361d22178ccb92ec26&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;809533e5b5c686e2d21b64361d22178ccb92ec26&lt;/a&gt; introduced a performance regression in the course of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-14304&quot; title=&quot;Avoid task starvation with mailbox&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-14304&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-14304&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The root cause seems to be the removal of the volatile variable for speed up the hotpath in case of an empty mailbox queue resulting in unnecessary lock acquisitions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
